project.context.localization.common.helper

Class WiFiMeasurement

  • java.lang.Object
    • project.context.localization.common.helper.WiFiMeasurement

  • public class WiFiMeasurement
extends java.lang.Object
    The WiFi measurement class can be seen as a struct. It holds the three basic information about a WiFi Access Point. SSID is the Name of a Network BSSI MAC address that identifies the Access Point RSSI is a measurement of the power present in the received radio signal of the AP
